{{see|bo}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Of Scandinavian origin. Old Norse [[búa]] = 'to live, to dwell'; Old Norse [[bú]] 'dwellingplace'.
Swedish verb 'att [[bo]]' = 'to live, to dwell'; Swedish noun [[bo]] = 'dweller; dwellingplace' cf. Stockholmbo = 'dweller of Stockholm'.

This name could also be a variant writing of the given name [[Beau]]. The name Beau comes from the French word [[beau]] = 'beautiful'. Cf. French Isabeau, side form of [[Isabelle]].

====Proper Noun====
'''Bo'''

# A male first name.

===Variants===
'''Beau'''

Cf. Mr. Beau Jangles, American dancer.

